    <div class="prose">
      <p>Running Rebuild is the easy part. The work that actually restores trust in the numbers is everything the damage left behind: reading the Verify error and QBWin.log to find what&rsquo;s actually broken, recovering transactions and lists that a standard rebuild can&rsquo;t resolve, reducing or condensing a file that has outgrown its limits, and re-running reconciliation until each account ties again. A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications does that against a written scope and verifies the file is clean before closing. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support; an Intuit account, login, or billing matter stays with Intuit.</p>
